Don’t do weird things with headers

  • Don;t start with a level-2 header (##) and later include a level-1 header (#)

  • Don’t skip header levels (though I think this isn’t an error per se)

[1]:

import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

[2]:

t = np.arange(2 * np.pi, step=.1)
plt.plot(t, np.sin(t))

[2]:
